<h1>Workshops</h1>
<p>
    Workshops will take place on 12th September. There are four main Workshops:
</p>
<h2>TOPICS IN APPLIED CRYPTOGRAPHY (TAC)</h2>
<b>Organizing Committee:</b>
<ul>
  <li>Marco Pedicini, Roma Tre University</li>
  <li>Veronica Cristiano, Telsy </li>
  <li>Alessandro Tomasi, Fondazione Bruno Kessler </li>
  <li>Chiara Spadafora, University of Trento</li>
  <li>Silvio Ranise, University of Trento</li>
  <li>Stefano Berlato, Fondazione Bruno Kessler</li>
</ul>
<b>Topics:</b>
<ul>
  <li>Privacy enhancing cryptography</li>
  <li>Homomorphic encryption</li>
  <li>Secure multi-party computation</li>
  <li>Quantum key distrbution and quantum-safe cryptography</li>
</ul>
<b>Confirmed speakers: </b> Peter Rønne, Université du Luxembourg
<br> <br>
<b>Call for submissions: </b> if you have a proposal for a talk or demo, please send an extended abstract of maximum 2 pages to <a href="mailto:tac@fbk.eu">tac<span>&#64;</span>fbk.eu</a>. There is no fixed deadline, as this call expects a rolling evaluation of submissions.
<br> <br>
For further information see our <a href="https://aleph.fbk.eu/events/TAC2025/">webpage</a>

